begin_memory_text: At the beginning we introduced ourselves. I had looked up some starter questions before the interview so started asking those as conversation starters. we kept it pretty simple.
middle_memory_text: In the middle she talked about her religion and where she stood on some topics. I kept asking questions to keep the conversation moving but she did most of the talking.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation we talked about what she was planning to do with her life. she wasn't sure if she wants to get married to a man or married to god. what i mean by that is become a nun
rest_of_day_open: I expect the rest of the week to go great. It is harvest season and all of the hard work i have put in is finally paying off. i am hoping to get it all harvested and finished by next weekend but if not then i will for sure next week. finally! the long wait is over.
critical_positive: I googled some conversation starter questions. I found one that had 250 different conversation starters and used that to keep the conversation moving as much as i could. It seemed to work. not on every question mind you but it was enough to keep us moving in the right direction.
critical_negative: It really went well so im struggling to find something that did not work. we had a few pauses a couple of times but i would say for the most part it went smoothly. even at its worst it was good in my mind.it felt like i interrupted her a few times but i caught myself later.
employ_7_TEXT: Half day and i run a small home business

begin_memory_text: We first introduced ourselves and he asked questions that he looked up. I remember the questions of what is your favorite number, actor, and what are you obsessed with?
middle_memory_text: There were more questions being asked, we talked about farms, farm work, what our business idea would be if we were to start one, about religion, Christianity in general, and some catholic teaching.
end_memory_text: We talked about the different vocations for Catholicism, Marriage and religious life. Nuns, roughly what it takes to become one. The fact that I am going to be exploring my personal calling to either religious life or marriage.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going pretty well, I'll probably be cooking dinners here and there and tending to my family in other ways as well as probably playing a lot of video games and spending time with my friends online, as well as having a good therapy session in there.
critical_positive: The conversation worked well because no one left an awkward pause in between, and we seemed to share a lot of similar views and background experiences. We also had a religion, Christianity, in common. He was also very kind, prepared to talk and I'm sure had a lot of experience with conversations.
critical_negative: There was moments when I wished he would just ditch the list and think of things for himself to talk about, it made it less organic though I tried my best to kind of steer things away from the list, he seemed to refer to it if there was ever a lull in the conversation.
